Score: 0.3
Reasoning: The recursive DP correctly counts ordered disjoint subsequence pairs by tracking (index, gcd1, gcd2), so the logic is functionally correct for small inputs. However, it can produce up to O(n * A^2) distinct memo states (A <= 200), which leads to very high time and memory usage; it will likely TLE or MLE on worst-case / large tests (n=200), so it won't pass all cases.
